<p>Label and Number: Self distributed; re-released on Saga 10.897<br>
Format: Cassette<br>
Year Released: 1983<br>
City, State, Country Released: Montréal, Québec, Canada <br>
Sephardic Songs:</p>
<p>
<a target="_blank" href="../De_fiestas_y_alegrias/La_novia_destrenza_el_pelo.sample.mp3">La novia destrenza el pelo</a><br>
Las quejas de Ximena<br>
La entrega de la Ley<br>
Abenámar<br>
La cena del desposado<br>
El testamento del rey Felipe<br>
Fray Pedro<br>
Cuando yo en ca de mi padre<br>
Gerineldo<br>
Esta noche de Purim<br>
Levantíme, madre<br>
Ni por cien navíos<br>
Búcar sobre Valencia<br>
Ansí se me arrimó<br>
El juicio del rey Salomón<br>
La partida del esposo<br>
Dize la nuestra novia</p>
<h3><font face="Verdana">Why this recording appears on our home page</font></h3>
<p>The Canadian group Gerineldo is one of the few performers to concentrate on 
the Moroccan repertory. Gerineldo's recordings were difficult to find in North 
America, but in Spain they were re-released on Saga, a prominent roots music 
label. Distributed in department and specialty shops, they came to the attention 
of the local folk community. Member Dr. Judith R. Cohen's work as a leading 
researcher has further heightened the profile of her recordings and those of 
Gerineldo as well.&nbsp; </p>
